SFemkMeG5Ach0Y8N-abgLh-MO6ee1sSE\" alt=\"\"></div>\n<ul>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">Get Real-time insights. The astounding speed and rise of big data in the market makes it hard to make strategic decisions on time. With AA, real-time actionable insights are presented to all users and decisions makers, with the speed in which it scans, analyses, sorts, and presents data faster than ever.&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</li>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">To avoid data overload. Big data is multiplying at an unprecedented rate and can easily backlog the operations of any enterprise. By investing in AA, users will no longer spend extensive time exploring data, as they can now instantly act on the most relevant insights that are prepared and presented to them. AA can help companies break down data into manageable insights.</span></li>\n</ul>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">Want to learn more about why your company should acquire augmented analytics? Discover the power of Augmented Analytics and how it has already delivered significant productivity gains of 350% and customer satisfaction gains of 60% by downloading the <a href=\"http://www.go.kpisoft.com/augmented-analytics-future-of-enterprise-performance\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">Gartner</a> report below.</span></p>\n<p><a href=\"http://www.go.kpisoft.com/augmented-analytics-future-of-enterprise-performance\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"https://www.go.kpisoft.com/hubfs/Imagea%201-1.jpg\" alt=\"Imagea 1-1\" width=\"600\" style=\"width: 600px; display: block; margin: 0px auto;\"></a></p>','Augmented Analytics vs Business Intelligence','','draft','closed','open','','','','','2018-06-13 10:45:11','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',0,'http://zensciences.com/kpisoft/?p=638',0,'post','',0),(639,1,'2018-06-12 12:00:14','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<p><span>&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">Albert Einstein once said, “If I were given one hour to save the planet, I would spend 59 minutes defining the problem and one minute resolving it.”&nbsp;<span style=\"background-color: transparent;\">Determining the problems your company faces can be as time consuming and puzzling as finding the solution to it, with less than 1% of the workforce being taught how to define problems. However, According to sources like&nbsp;</span><a href=\"https://www.forbes.com/sites/cherylsnappconner/2013/03/04/the-8-great-challenges-every-business-faces-and-how-to-master-them-all/\" style=\"font-size: 18px; background-color: transparent;\">Forbes</a><span style=\"background-color: transparent;\">,&nbsp;</span><a href=\"https://www.hiscox.co.uk/business-blog/the-10-biggest-challenges-businesses-face-today-and-need-consultants-for/\" style=\"font-size: 18px; background-color: transparent;\">HISCOX</a><span style=\"background-color: transparent;\">&nbsp;and the&nbsp;</span><a href=\"https://www.leanmethods.com/resources/articles/top-ten-problems-faced-business/\" style=\"font-size: 18px; background-color: transparent;\">Lean Methods Group</a><span style=\"background-color: transparent;\">, there are 5 key problems almost all enterprises face.</span></span></p>\n<!--more-->\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\"><strong>5 key problems all enterprises face:</strong></span></p>\n<ol>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">Uncertainty</span></li>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">Monitoring Performance</span></li>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">Information overload</span></li>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">Problem Solving and Risk Management.</span></li>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">Technology</span></li>\n</ol>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">These problems may sound familiar and often unsolvable, however can be simply avoided through the use of Augmented Analytics. Here are the ways that Augmented Analytics can solve your top 5 problems for you:</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 20px;\"><strong>How Augmented Analytics can solve each problem?</strong></span></p>\n<ol>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\"><strong>Technology </strong></span></li>\n</ol>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\"><strong>The problem:</strong> According to <a href=\"https://www.computerworld.com/article/2502348/it-management/it-jobs-will-grow-22--through-2020--says-u-s-.html\">ComputerWorld</a>, IT jobs will increase by 22% by 2020. However, this does not mean the company’s overall understanding of technology will grow simultaneously. With the high speed pace of technology, many business can get left behind or overtaken by more tech-savvy companies. “There’s no doubt that life and business have gotten more complex, even as certain tasks and activities have become easier due to information technology” explains Lean Methods Group. A sizeable amount of companies currently rely on DS and their IT department to handle the data and it’s governance, however as stated in the Gartner Report, by 2020 there will be more CDS than DS, and the organizations that offer access to a curated catalog of internal and external data will derive 2 times the business value from analytics investments, as compared to those that do not.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\"><strong>The solution:</strong> Why the benefits of CDS is so prominent is due to the ways in which Augmented Analytics tackle the issues of complex technology. One way is through the use of Natural Language Generation (NLG), a software systems that automatically generates narratives and reports, in easy-to-read language, which describes, summarizes and explains input data to any user. NLG is a type of Natural Language Processing (NLP), which comprises all software that interprets or produces human language, in either spoken or written form. There are four key types of NLP: NLG, Natural Language Understanding, Speech synthesis, and speech recognition. All these tools helps collaborate, analyse, simply and present data to those who would benefit off it, making everyone in a business a CDS. As a result of this, companies no longer have a bottleneck system to gain insights and understanding for the IT department, and hence workers will become proficient in the decisions they make and the time it takes to make it.</span></p>\n<div><img src=\"https://www.go.kpisoft.com/hubfs/augmented%20analytics.jpg\" alt=\"augmented analytics\" width=\"2000\" style=\"width: 2000px; margin: 0px 10px 10px 0px;\"></div>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\"><span style=\"background-color: transparent;\">2. </span><strong style=\"background-color: transparent;\">Uncertainty</strong></span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\"><strong>The problem:</strong> With almost every day to day decision based on contingency; probabilities and probability distributions are the soul to the fundamental laws of nature and the way businesses function.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\"><strong>The Solution:</strong> Instead of depending on probability and the expected/predicted numbers of sale or expected revenue, Machine Learning and Artificial Intelligence (AI) algorithms can predict a full probability distribution. Each specific choice of a number derived from this distribution is associated with a specific outcome. This allows you to assess all the possible options for the future, each linked with a specific probability, giving you the ability to fully explore the benefits and impacts of all operational decisions with scientific precision.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">Data Science (DS) and Machine Learning helps enable business users and Citizen Data Scientists (CDS) to automatically find, visualise, and narrate relevant findings, such as correlations, expectations, clusters and predictions. This not only helps your company deal with uncertainties, but accelerates the time to obtain these accurate insights.This reduces the risk of missing important insights in the data compared to manual exploration</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">3. <strong>Monitoring Performance</strong></span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\"><strong>The Problem:</strong> <a href=\"https://www.inc.com/michael-olguin/4-reasons-you-need-to-set-business-goals.html\">The importance of setting goals in a business</a> is extremely significant, and Key Performance Indicators (KPIs) are measurable values that demonstrate how effectively a company is achieving the key business goals. KPI’s include contextualized individual actionable insights related to the performance of the enterprise. Many companies struggle monitoring these activities, as monitoring what is unmeasurable makes improvement improbable.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\"><strong>The Solution: </strong>With Augmented Analytics, KPIs can be measured, monitored, presented and shared, allowing not only CEO’s to view their companies performance, but every individual viewing their own, which at large helps the company reach their goals. With real-time awareness of performance, encouraging collaboration and corrective action, the efficiency, motivation and knowledge of the entire business escalates.</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;<span style=\"font-size: 18px;\"><span style=\"background-color: transparent;\">4. </span><strong style=\"background-color: transparent;\">Information overload</strong></span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\"><strong>The problem: </strong>Though gaining accurate information can be a struggle in companies, one of the top problems is the overload of it, and what to do with it. It doesn’t matter how much information you have, if your company can\'t decipher what it means, what to do with it, and how to organise it.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\"><strong>The Solution:</strong> Augmented Analytics and Augmented Data Discovery helps go through all the data, detecting patterns, correlations, and outliers; and presents only what is relevant. Overall, Augmented Analytics can help present data to you in an organised and simplified way, so that all users understand what they are looking at, and no longer feel lost in the colossal amount of information. Augmented Analytics can reduce the consumption of exploration and the identification of false or less relevant insights.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">5. <strong>Problem Solving and Risk Management.</strong></span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\"><strong>The Problem:</strong> A major problem companies face is finding reasonable and fitting solutions, that consider their brand image, financial status, and resources. One wrong decision can lead to a chain of unwanted consequences, and hence the reasoning behind each verdict is momentous. How can a company know if their decisions are validated? What resources do they currently have to assist these judgments?</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\"><strong>The Solution: </strong>Machine learning algorithms use something called “gradient descent,” a system that gradually improves a solution by reducing its error. A type of problem Machine Learning can solve can be Financial analysis. Machine learning will enable continual assessments of data for detection and analysis of anomalies and nuances to improve the precision of models and rules. In this way, Augmented Analytics can be a personalized anchor to any business, assisting all decisions made, ensuring that the company is presented with all the possibilities, risks, and information needed to guide them in the right direction.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">There are infinite possibilities of problems businesses can face, regardless of their size, field, or success. By knowing the 5 key things almost all enterprises face, and applying it to your business, not only are you being put in the right direction, but are given a head start to rectifying it. With the help of Augmented Analytics, the process of solving your problems will be as fast as identifying it. Problems that are so recurrent and common in even the most prestigious companies, can now be tackled with the right resources and understanding.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">Don’t stop here - <a href=\"http://www.go.kpisoft.com/augmented-analytics-future-of-enterprise-performance\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">Download</a> the Gartner Report to further explore the possibilities of AI and the importance of tracking KPIs for your business.</span></p>\n<p><a href=\"http://www.go.kpisoft.com/augmented-analytics-future-of-enterprise-performance\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\"><img src=\"https://www.go.kpisoft.com/hubfs/Imagea%201-1.jpg\" alt=\"augmented analytics\" width=\"600\" style=\"width: 600px; display: block; margin: 0px auto;\"></span></a></p>','Top 5 problems in a business - How Augmented Analytics can solve it','','draft','closed','open','','','','','2018-06-12 12:00:14','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',0,'http://zensciences.com/kpisoft/?p=639',0,'post','',0),(640,1,'2018-06-06 12:01:45','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<p><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\"><img src=\"https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/bI_3imu-tO596LIcBuXyRAixAHWLZt9SEYP-a13B8sJZ064_BWE3Y77VQFzlZ-UCPA07SbyaAr1hMt0gJIzpUKhKfB_t4-meBfYdyLbONIa6lLpsQbKSt_3s6-IU4IURxNeWhocG\" alt=\"data democratization\" style=\"background-color: transparent; width: 1283px; margin: 0px 10px 10px 0px;\" width=\"1283\"></span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\"><span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;For decades, companies have faced issues of miscommunication, the hierarchy of decisions making, and the scarcity of relevant information.&nbsp;</span></span></p>\n<!--more-->\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">Data, something that benefits every department and individual in an enterprise, is often clustered and governed by one body, the IT department, and Data Scientists. To be able to democratization vital data throughout the company would mean that every single user would have the ability to enquire, understand, apply and make action plans at a rate far beyond their previous. Though it undoubtedly surgers auspiciously better results due to several factors, this article will address 2 Key reasons why your enterprise needs Data Democratization.</span></p>\n<p><strong style=\"font-size: 20px; background-color: transparent;\">1. To suit the emerging workforce consisting of Millennials</strong></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">Psychological studies time after time show that millennials need to be reassured much more than the average Baby Boomer or Generation X’ers. This does not mean their age group seeks constant praise and guidance, rather feedback and score on where they are in their career, respective to their company’s goals. Millennials grew up in the era of IT and the Internet, hence their constant need for instant answers is driven in their system. Feedback motivates millennials because they feel safe (in regard to being lost), due to their brain being wired to the educational system of always being guided. This educational system mentality is much more prominent in millennials as&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www2.deloitte.com/insights/us/en/economy/issues-by-the-numbers/understanding-millennials-generational-differences.html\">studies</a>&nbsp;show they are the generation who receives the most education. The college enrollment rate among millennials in all age groups is higher than the rate for either older generation. Completion rates are also increasing, with 39.4 percent of those starting at a four-year institution in 2007 graduating in four years and 59.4 percent graduating within six years. These higher levels of educational attainment at ages 21 to 36 suggest that Millennials – especially Millennial women – are on track to be our most educated generation by the time they complete their educational journeys.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">This should not be confused with the idea that millennials are not independent or self-sufficient. The reason they require such strong communication is because millennials visualize their performance, and the targets they have met or yet to meet, so that they can feel in control, and can then re adjust their work in order to reach goals or continue being successful. This is because based on a study over 100 countries, one common trait among millennials is that “they trust themselves most to solve local challenges” (Rappler.com, 2016)</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">Why they need for instant information? Their inclined nature to refer to the internet to gain instant knowledge reflects in their working habits to always need to be up to date. If a business is not up to date on systems that can enhance communication around the office and the management of KPIs, millennials tend to feel dissatisfied and frustrated. Hence it is important for enterprises to develop and grow in correlation to the advancement in the IT world, as this integration can aid these very problems, strengthening the gratification they will have towards the company. Their loyalty should not be underestimated, and great attention should be given to it. 28% of workers ages 18-35 say they can see themselves staying on for at least another two years, which can be due to their constant need to seek fulfillment and regain their motivation. If they can however view their performance in their current company, the need to start over can be avoided, as millennials like to feel in control and in the right direction.</span></p>\n<div><img src=\"https://www.go.kpisoft.com/hubfs/The%20Millennials%20inforgraphic.png\" alt=\"The Millennials inforgraphic\"></div>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 20px;\"><strong><span style=\"background-color: transparent;\">2.</span></strong><strong style=\"background-color: transparent;\"> The integration from data scientists, to citizen data scientists, yields increase efficiency</strong></span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; font-size: 18px;\">With Augmented Analytics, Citizen Data Scientists (CDS) will receive real time analysis, meaning business users and CDS to automatically find, visualize, and narrate relevant findings; such as correlations, expectations, clusters and predictions. A study by IBM found that key executives globally spend 70 percent of their time finding data and only 30 percent analyzing it. On top of that, research indicates that 99 percent of new data is never used, analyzed or transformed. Receiving information allows employees to validate themselves, make decisions, or improve their performance, making them feel either confident/ important or productive. Through this, they are gaining Non Financial Rewards (Fringe benefits) like job enlargement (through the extra tasks they can now control and conduct) and job enrichment (through the increase in skill and responsibility they are given).</span></p>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div><span style=\"font-size: 18px; background-color: transparent;\">This in return will enhance their motivation and increase the efficiency levels in all departments. This is linked to the fact that real time analysis and constant information of performance allows constant improvements and decision. Just like the commonly understood method of Kaizen (Japanese for constant “improvement”), and how making changes and monitoring results, then adjusting these actions can create a chain of improvement. Large-scale pre-planning and extensive project scheduling are replaced by smaller experiments, which can be rapidly adapted as new improvements are suggested.This allows employees to make independent decisions based off their specialised knowledge, and what works best for them.</span></div>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">Just because the IT department has the data, does not mean they possess the knowledge of how it should be utilized. By allowing individuals with a range of skills to have access to data that directly benefits and is understood by them can increase the time taken to make decisions, and the use of each employees knowledge&nbsp;</span></p>','Are you in the loop?: Top Reasons why Data Democratization delivers better performance','','draft','closed','open','','','','','2018-06-06 12:01:45','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',0,'http://zensciences.com/kpisoft/?p=640',0,'post','',0),(641,1,'2017-06-05 12:26:56','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<p style=\"line-height: 1em;\"><img src=\"http://www.go.kpisoft.com/hubfs/sandra.jpg\" alt=\"sandra.jpg\" style=\"background-color: transparent; width: 1024px;\" width=\"1024\"></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">Dr. Pereira, reflecting on her own career over the past 20 years, shares her advice with IT engineers at the beginning as well as more mature stages of their work life. In this interview with Atmarkit, the leading media for IT professionals in Japan, Sandra talks about approaches in dealing with career changes, cross functional experiences, the importance of setting goals and thoughts on&nbsp;leadership;</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">After studying medicine at Goethe&nbsp;University and becoming a clinician, she turned to a consultant. McKinsey &amp; Company moved to Pharmaceuticals and Healthcare, and as a Human Resources Development Consultant to Germany, UK, and Singapore. I am involved in setting up Saudi Arabia office.&nbsp;</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\"> In January 2017, assumed office as Kpisoft CEO.&nbsp;She is also a working mother with two children.</span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><!--more--><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\"><strong style=\"background-color: transparent;\">I am a Global Citizen</strong><span style=\"background-color: transparent;\">- an interview with Hisahiro Abe.&nbsp;</span></span></p>\n<p><img src=\"http://www.go.kpisoft.com/hubfs/sandra%202.jpg\" alt=\"sandra 2.jpg\" width=\"1024\" style=\"width: 1024px;\"></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">Germany, UK, Singapore, Saudi Arabia - What female consultants who have worked in various countries advise and how to deal with new things?&nbsp;\"What is important is to enjoy the work you are doing from the bottom of your heart\" said Dr. Sandra Pereira</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\"><strong>Hospital and KPI</strong></span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">Hisahiro Abe (hereinafter, <strong>Abe River</strong>)&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 18px; background-color: transparent;\">Have you been born in Frankfurt?&nbsp;What was your major in Goethe University?</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\"><strong>Sandra Pereira</strong> (Hereafter, Pereira) This is a pediatric doctor (MD: Doctor of Medicine).&nbsp;I think that it became a human-centered way of thinking by directly touching on human\'s life.&nbsp;I actually worked 3 years as a clinician. I moved to&nbsp;McKinsey ... ....&nbsp;I think that I chose a very different path, what happened? (Lol)</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\"><strong>Mrs. Pereira</strong> is always asked, Why the person why the doctor became a consultant? (Laugh).</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">In fact, 40% of McKinsey employees are gatherings of consultants with various backgrounds.&nbsp;McKinsey is a company that values the diversity of the team, and it is because he wanted a person with a career like me to realize the very diversity.&nbsp;I myself jumped into the world of a business consultant from a doctor of a hospital, I learned that the different individuals raise each other\'s abilities and create strength as a team.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\"><strong>Abe River</strong>-Anyway, why did you want to transform into a business world?</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\"><strong>Mrs. Pereira</strong> was a college student\'s&nbsp;experience.&nbsp;At one time, \"KPI (*)\" was introduced by the insurance company to the pediatric ward where I worked.&nbsp;The mission of the hospital is to cure the patient\'s illness, but suddenly the financial goal has fallen.&nbsp;The director of the hospital was very puzzled because he had never managed the hospital from such a point of view.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\"><strong>Abe River</strong>-Hospital is an organization.&nbsp;It is necessary to operate.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\"><strong>Mrs. Pereira</strong> Yes.&nbsp;The parties to hospital management are \"doctors\", \"patients\" and \"insurance companies\", but doctors do not care about financial matters at all.&nbsp;Insurance companies are involved in the operation.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">With the introduction of KPI, we focused on \"whether this department and treatment is within budget\" although we have operated hospitals mainly for patients.&nbsp;For that reason, I do not know how much important decisions were postponed and unreasonable decisions were made.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">Of course, you cannot diagnose the patient just by knowledge of finance.&nbsp;However, if financial restrictions exist, patients will be bent.&nbsp;When I thought that there should be a way to balance the two things \"seeing patients\" and \"running the hospital\" somewhere, I got a story saying, \"Why do not you try as a consultant?\"&nbsp;McKinsey set the light on my inquisitive spirit.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">* Key Performance Indicators (KPI) Key performance indicators.&nbsp;Numbers to measure if the process is being executed properly towards organizational goals. </span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> Visit us at <a href=\"https://www.kpisoft.com/\">kpisoft.com</a> and <a href=\"http://www.go.kpisoft.com/schedule-performange-management-best-practices-demo\">schedule a demo</a>.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><a href=\"https://www.kpisoft.com/\"><img src=\"http://www.go.kpisoft.com/hubfs/new_blog_logo-4.png\" alt=\"new_blog_logo-4.png\" width=\"521\" height=\"225\" style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"></a></span></p>','“Enjoy the work you are doing from the bottom of your heart”','','draft','closed','open','','','','','2017-06-05 12:26:56','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',0,'http://zensciences.com/kpisoft/?p=641',0,'post','',0),(642,1,'2017-05-26 09:54:47','2017-05-26 09:54:47','<p style=\"line-height: 1em;\"><img src=\"http://www.go.kpisoft.com/hubfs/performance.jpg\" alt=\"performance.jpg\" width=\"1024\" style=\"width: 1024px;\"></p>\n<span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">Yes, it is that time of the year again when several companies will begin the process of the mid-year performance review.&nbsp; Managers and employees will spend a large amount of time and effort reviewing the previous six months’ performance against competencies, goals and objectives.&nbsp; The cost of this exercise not to mention the lost revenue opportunities or cost savings in earlier months now become a reality.&nbsp; All too little too late.</span>\n<!--more--><span style=\"background-color: transparent; font-size: 18px;\">During my career as a human resource&nbsp;professional, I\'ve been focused on finding a solution that can replace the traditional way of handling the dreaded annual review proc