lt, and ask a question about how they see the topic to encourage comments and conversation. Don\'t forget to include a Call-to-Action!</p>\n<p>Congratulations! What a lovely list post you\'ve created!</p><br /><hr />\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n','List-Based Post [Blogging Blueprint]','','draft','closed','open','','','','','2015-11-16 21:39:57','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',0,'http://zensciences.com/kpisoft/?p=690',0,'post','',0),(691,1,'2015-11-06 19:08:14','0000-00-00 00:00:00','\n<hr />\n<p><strong>INTRODUCTION:</strong></p>\n<p>An image post uses a visual element as the centerpiece of your post, such as a SlideShare presentation, infographic, comic, or high-resolution images.</p>\n<p>Use your introduction to provide a caption for your image(s). Why is it valuable? What’s the point? Image posts don’t require a lot of text, so choose your words wisely.</p>\n<p>Here are some examples of how we use Visual blog posts here at HubSpot:</p>\n<li><a href=\"http://blog.hubspot.com/marketing/google-algorithm-visual-history-infographic\">A Visual History of Google Algorithm Changes [Infographic]</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"http://blog.hubspot.com/marketing/career-b2b-marketing-fulfilling-slideshare\">Can a Career in B2B Marketing Be Fulfilling? [SlideShare]</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"http://blog.hubspot.com/marketing/sexiest-business-blogs-internet-list\">A Sampling of the Sexiest Business Blogs on the Internet</a></li>\n<!--more-->\n<hr />\n<p><strong>BODY:</strong></p>\n<br />After just a few lines of introductory text, insert the visual.\n<p><strong><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; width: 420px;\" title=\"image-068859-edited\" src=\"http://cdn2.hubspot.net/hub/0/file-0-png/example.png\" alt=\"image-068859-edited\" width=\"420\"></strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Call out the most important elements of the visual. Include “Tweet this!” links that mention key points and vital takeaways from your visual. <br /><br /></p>\n<hr />\n<p><br /><strong>CONCLUSION:</stron